A lone figure in a tattered cloak stands at the edge of the cliff, holding a glowing crystal that pulses with pale blue light. Below, the ocean crashes against the rocks in shimmering, bioluminescent waves. In the sky above, glowing constellations form the shape of a mythical phoenix mid-flight, its wings made of stardust and fire. The scene is tranquil yet filled with wonder, as if the world is holding its breath.

Surfaces are clean and polished with subtle textures—moss, stone, fabric, and ocean mist rendered with digital precision. Lighting is ambient and ethereal—cool tones from the sky balanced by the soft glow of the crystal and phoenix, with gentle rim light on the figure. The atmosphere is dreamlike, charged with mystery, nostalgia, and ancient magic. Not overly yellow, painterly, or grainy.
